This paper deals with the problem of randomized matching algorithms, which is a topic in both discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and theoretical computer science (cs.DS). The paper also involves the analysis of approximation ratios, which is a common theme in algorithmic game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper uses probabilistic techniques to analyze the performance of the algorithms, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
